      • launchRealAndroidApp

        public static void launchRealAndroidApp(java.lang.String appName)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Launch app based on appName. This will assist to launch multiple app with different appPackage/appActivity capabilities within same test script scope

        Ex:"flipkart". This App name passed will concat with AppPackage/AppActivity string. The resulting string variable value is retrieved from config.properties file and will automatically launch the app/driver session
        Parameters:
        appName - the app name. Ex:"flipkart" or"fk" or anything which is exactly same as variable name in config.properties file
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - the exception

        yEnd - the y end coordinates
        swipeTime - the sweep time
        totalSwipes - the total swipes

      • scrollFindAndClickOnElement

        public static void scrollFindAndClickOnElement(org.openqa.selenium.By byElementLocator,
                                               int repeatSwipe)
                                        throws java.lang.Exception
        Find and click on element.
        Step 1: If Element is not found then do 'Swipe Up' and try again to find element.
        Step 2: Repeat step 1 process until element is found. Worst case, repeat 'Swipe and Find' process for limit specified by 'repeatSwipe'

        As compared to 'scrollToAndClickOnElement()' works for all kinds of By Locator. But, starts swiping screen from current till end of page. Hence, if the element is above current screen then it won't find the element.
        Parameters:
        byElementLocator - the by element locator. Ex: "By.className(String className)"
        repeatSwipe - Total swipe to be done. Tries to find an element after Swipe is done each time.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - the exception
